The paper presents a new model for dyadic prediction that can handle both ordinal and nominal labels, and can exploit side-information if present. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
